(71, 3, '2012-06-01 05:54:37', '2012-06-01 05:54:37', '<a href="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120531-193913.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full" src="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120531-193913.jpg" alt="20120531-193913.jpg" /></a>\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>ali:</strong></span> traveling is my passion. I love the opportunity for discovery that it provides. I often claim that most of the decisions I make in life are guided by the  desire to have good stories to tell over dinner. I am only half joking. After losing all I owned, I once hitchhiked from Costa Rica to Arizona. I''ve slept in the same room as a green mamba - which, upon discovery, I ate. After participating in a local ceremony for warriors in West Africa, the traditional healer assures me that I am bullet-proof. I also like warm milk with cinnamon before bed, laughing until I cry, dancing without inhibition (and better yet, in costume!), and picking scabs until they bleed.\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>adam:</strong></span> i love music. listening and making. especially with others. i ride my bike a lot. been hit thrice since i moved to st. louis. once i rode from london to budapest. people were friendly and cars didn''t run over me. i camped in parks and slept on strangers floors. i came back with a knowledge of how much i''d taken ranch dressing and obesity for granted. i''m a huge fan of wikipedia and npr. i am not usually very good at making decisions, my spelling is atrocious, and i add a few centimeters when i tell people how tall i am.', 'adam & ali', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-autosave', '', '', '2012-06-01 05:54:37', '2012-06-01 05:54:37', '', 2, 'http://anywherethewindblows.com/?p=71', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
