(81, 2, '2012-06-04 18:19:59', '2012-06-04 18:19:59', 'five airports, four cities, three flights, and one day later, adam and i find ourselves in london.  \r\n\r\nyesterday, we spent (a far insufficient) three hours roaming the streets (and subways) of NYC.  We ate dollar pizza, met up with a friend at a beautiful hotel, and absorbed the frenetic energy of downtown.  new york is big, loud, busy, dirty, and yet against all odds, surprisingly friendly - fittingly iconic of america(ns).  i am so looking forward to our return there in august.\r\n\r\nSandwiched between two overnight flights, we visited one of my dearest friends, Leslie, in London. The city was buzzing with excitement over the queen''s jubilee weekend. In honor or such a lofty occasion, les greeted us with a traditional English tea.  It turns out that "clotted cream" isn''t nearly as disgusting as the name would lead one to believe.  We spent the day exploring east London, relishing in the rare moments of sunlight, and,naturally, eating. \r\n\r\n<br /><br /><a href="http://anywherethewindblows.com/?page_id=102"><img src="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120603-073919.jpg" alt="20120603-073919.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a>\r\n\r\n<br /><br /><a href="http://anywherethewindblows.com/?page_id=102"><img src="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120603-073845.jpg" alt="20120603-073845.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a>\r\n\r\n<br /><br /><a href="http://anywherethewindblows.com/?page_id=102"><img src="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120603-073826.jpg" alt="20120603-073826.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a>\r\n\r\n<br /><br /><a href="http://anywherethewindblows.com/?page_id=102"><img src="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120603-073854.jpg" alt="20120603-073854.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a>\r\n\r\n<br /><br /><a href="http://anywherethewindblows.com/?page_id=102"><img src="h