(182, 3, '2012-06-04 18:13:03', '2012-06-04 18:13:03', 'A sleepless night of packing, followed by two consecutive nights of dozing  in airports and planes, we arrived in Mumbai exhausted in the early evening of our third full day of traveling.  We splurged and spent an extra $2 on a taxi with AC.  Worth every rupee.  The hour long ride to our hotel  was both dreadful and amazing.  Five lanes of cars, motorbikes, and autorickshaws, all pushing their way down a three lane road, making their presence known with a near constant buzz of their horns.  With automobiles so tightly packed, I could have, at any time, reached over and honked the horn of the car next to us.  Please keep your arms in the vehicle at all times.  If you want to keep them that is.  After depositing our packs at the Royal Castle Hotel, we went out to take in the city.  Mumbai is fantastic.  Vibrant, dirty, teaming with people, and nearly apathetic of our existence.\r\n\r\nToday we awoke early (unable to sleep due to jet lag) and did a bit more roaming, looking for something delicious for breakfast and a strong cup of coffee.  Afterwards we packed up our belongings and grabbed a taxi to the India Guest House in Colaba.  The 20 minute, un-air conditioned ride made me glad we''d opted for AC on the previous day.  After checking in, we again hit the city, wandering past the famous Taj Mahal Hotel and into the Gateway of India where we arranged for a taxi to drive us to all of the obligatory tourist stops: Dhobi Ghaat, open air laundry; Worli Fishing Village; Mani Bhavan Gandhi Museum; etc...  We came back to the hotel early and took a long, much need nap, before heading out for our first true Indian dining experience.  Paneer Tikka Masala for me and Vegetable Korma for Ali.  Absolutely delicious.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120604-231052.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full" src="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120604-231052.jpg" alt="20120604-231052.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120604-231101.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full" src="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120604-231101.jpg" alt="20120604-231101.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120604-231109.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full" src="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120604-231109.jpg" alt="20120604-231109.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120604-231115.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full" src="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120604-231115.jpg" alt="20120604-231115.jpg" /></a>', 'india is great.  horn ok please.', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '176-revision-4', '', '', '2012-06-04 18:13:03', '2012-06-04 18:13:03', '', 176, 'http://anywherethewindblows.com/?p=182', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(184, 2, '2012-06-03 07:02:37', '2012-06-03 07:02:37', 'five airports, four cities, three flights, and one day later, adam and i find ourselves in london.  \n\nyesterday, we spent (a far insufficient) three hours roaming the streets (and subways) of NYC.  We ate dollar pizza, met up with a friend at a beautiful hotel, and absorbed the frenetic energy of downtown.  new york is big, loud, busy, dirty, and yet against all odds, surprisingly friendly - fittingly iconic of america(ns).  i am so looking forward to our return there in august.\n\nSandwiched between two overnight flights, we visited one of my dearest friends, Leslie, in London. The city was buzzing with excitement over the queen''s jubilee weekend. In honor or such a lofty occasion, les greeted us with a traditional English tea.  It turns out that "clotted cream" isn''t nearly as disgusting as the name would lead one to believe.  We spent the day exploring east London, relishing in the rare moments of sunlight, and,naturally, eating. \n\n<br /><br /><a href="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120603-073919.jpg"><img src="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120603-073919.jpg" alt="20120603-073919.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120603-073845.jpg"><img src="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120603-073845.jpg" alt="20120603-073845.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120603-073826.jpg"><img src="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120603-073826.jpg" alt="20120603-073826.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120603-073854.jpg"><img src="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120603-073854.jpg" alt="20120603-073854.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a>\n\n<br /><br /><a href="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120603-100100.jpg"><img src="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120603-100100.jpg" alt="20120603-100100.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120603-100114.jpg"><img src="http://anywherethewindblows.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/20120603-100114.jpg" alt="20120603-100114.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a>', 'five airports, four cities, three flights, and one day later', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '79-revision-10', '', '', '2012-06-03 07:02:37', '2012-06-03 07:02:37', '', 79, 'http://anywherethewindblows.com/?p=184', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
