(557, 2, '2012-07-04 09:09:31', '2012-07-04 09:09:31', 'Traveling is a tiring endeavor.  At the end of most days what we want most is a soft place to lay our heads and a good night''s sleep.  Frequently we settle for just a night''s sleep (good or otherwise).  On occasion we are handed a couple of hours of dozing in 15 minute increments sitting upright on a 12 hour, bumpy, loud, overnight bus ride to our next destination.  A good night of sleep is occasionally forfeited by budget travelers in order to save a few bucks or to gain an extra day of sightseeing at the expense of overnight transportation.  Sometimes is just the price one pays for a good adventure.  Our trip thus far has been no exception.  We''ve slept on airplanes, in buses, on benches in airports, in tents on the beach, and even on the deck of a boat.  There has been no shortage of variety in our sleeping accommodations throughout our trip.  So it was fitting that we ended up on one of Southeast Asia''s most notorious bus rides on the evening of the last day in June.  A 28 hour journey crossing the Vietnam/Laos border and winding through the jungle clad mountains of northern Laos.  In honor of our one month anniversary of traveling, I''ve put together the following illustrations.\r\n\r\n</br></br>\r\n\r\n[easychart type="pie" title="where we slept in june" groupnames="Hotels/Hostels,Tent,Airport,Bus,Airplane,Homestay/Monestary,Boat" group1values="16" group2values="3" group3values="3" group4values="3" group5values="2" group6values="2" group7values="1" chartfadecolor="FFFFFF"]\r\n\r\n</br></br>\r\n\r\n[easychart type="horizbarstack" height="50" width="200" title="nights slept on a mattress" groupnames="Hotels/Hostels,Tent,Airport,Bus,Airplane,Homestay/Monestary,Boat" valuenames="no mattress,mattress" group1values="0,16" group2values="3,0" group3values="3,0" group4values="3,0" group5values="2,0" group6values="2,0" group7values="0,1"]\r\n', 'A place to rest our heads', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '516-revision-31', '', '', '2012-07-04 09:09:31', '2012-07-04 09:09:31', '', 516, 'http://anywherethewindblows.com/?p=557', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(558, 2, '2012-07-04 09:12:42', '2012-07-04 09:12:42', 'Traveling is a tiring endeavor.  At the end of most days what we want most is a soft place to lay our heads and a good night''s sleep.  Frequently we settle for just a night''s sleep (good or otherwise).  On occasion we are handed a couple of hours of dozing in 15 minute increments sitting upright on a 12 hour, bumpy, loud, overnight bus ride to our next destination.  A good night of sleep is occasionally forfeited by budget travelers in order to save a few bucks or to gain an extra day of sightseeing by taking overnight transportation.  Sometimes it''s just the price one pays for a good adventure.  Our trip thus far has been no exception.  We''ve slept on airplanes, in buses, on benches in airports, in tents on the beach, and even on the deck of a boat.  There has been no shortage of variety in our sleeping accommodations throughout our trip.  So it was fitting that we ended up on one of Southeast Asia''s most notorious bus rides on the evening of the last day in June.  A 28 hour journey crossing the Vietnam/Laos border and winding through the jungle clad mountains of northern Laos.  In honor of our one month anniversary of traveling, I''ve put together the following illustrations.\r\n\r\n</br></br>\r\n\r\n[easychart type="pie" title="where we slept in june" groupnames="Hotels/Hostels,Tent,Airport,Bus,Airplane,Homestay/Monestary,Boat" group1values="16" group2values="3" group3values="3" group4values="3" group5values="2" group6values="2" group7values="1" chartfadecolor="FFFFFF"]\r\n\r\n</br></br>\r\n\r\n[easychart type="horizbarstack" height="50" width="200" title="nights slept on a mattress" groupnames="Hotels/Hostels,Tent,Airport,Bus,Airplane,Homestay/Monestary,Boat" valuenames="no mattress,mattress" group1values="0,16" group2values="3,0" group3values="3,0" group4values="3,0" group5values="2,0" group6values="2,0" group7values="0,1"]\r\n', 'A place to rest our heads', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '516-rev